    <main class="post-detail container">
        <img src="images/PatriotsSoccer.jpg" alt="Picture of Men's soccer celebrating" class="post-hero">
        <figcaption>Photo credit: University of the Cumberlands</figcaption>
        <p> The #8 Women's Soccer team opened their 2025 campaign with a strong performance against Missouri Baptist University winning 5-0.  </p>
        <p> Abigail Little, Juano Fernandez Calvo, Carola Fontan, Nicole Araujo, and Wakana Ose all scored in the first half.  </p>
        <p>The Patriots held on in the second half to maintain the clean sheet. They would get off 23 shots on the day with 11 being on goal. Morgan White started in goal and would play 81 minutes making one save. Ella Gilliam filled in the last 9 minutes to preserve the clean sheet. </p>
        <p> The #4 Men’s Soccer team opened up their campaign with a 1-1 draw on the road at Grace College. The teams would play to a 0-0 first half. The second half would be more eventful for the two teams. 18 minutes into the half and Samuel Dolobaipu would put the Pats up 1-0. Grace College would tie it up and neither team would find a game winning goal.</p>
        <p> The NAIA would announce the preseason rankings for both Men's and Women's Cross Country teams. Both programs would come in at #4 in the country. </p>
        <p> This is the highest ranking for women's in the preseason poll ever. Both programs begin their season next Friday at the Berea College Jamboree. </p>
       
